Prince Rashed, Princess Zeina welcome baby boy

Amman, Feb. 2 (Petra)--The Royal Court announced that Their Royal Highnesses Prince Rashed Bin Al Hassan and Princess Zeina Rashid were blessed with a baby boy.

The Royal Court said the baby, born on Monday, February 1, 2016 ( Rabi II 22, 1437 Hijri), was named Talal.

PRINCESS ZEINA RASHID OF JORDAN JOINS AS NEW GOVERNING BOARD MEMBER

07. August 2020

We are delighted to announce that Her Royal Highness Princess Zeina Rashid of Jordan is joining the ITTF Foundation family as a new Governing Board member.

The former table tennis player, who competed at the Athens 2004 and Beijing 2008 Olympic Games, has continued to be heavily involved in sport and currently sits on the Jordan Olympic Committee as a member of the Board of Directors.

The 32-year-old is also in charge of the programme “20 for Tokyo 2020”, an ambitious plan put in place by the Jordan Olympic Committee with the goal of having 20 athletes from the Middle East nation qualify for Tokyo.
